<i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Politics_of_Experience\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Politics of Experience\">The Politics of Experience</a></i> (Penguin 1984)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Metanoia_(psychology)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20120426061656/http://jungiancenter.org/essay/jung%E2%80%99s-timeliness-and-thoughts-our-current-reality\">\"Achieving a Metanoia\"</a>. <i>Jungian Center News</i>. 2009-07-06. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://jungiancenter.org/essay/jung%E2%80%99s-timeliness-and-thoughts-our-current-reality\">the original</a> on 2012-04-26<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2010-01-20</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Jungian+Center+News&amp;rft.atitle=Achieving+a+Metanoia&amp;rft.date=2009-07-06&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fjungiancenter.org%2Fessay%2Fjung%25E2%2580%2599s-timeliness-and-thoughts-our-current-reality&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMetanoia+%28psychology%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2242\nCached time: 20180921192914\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.188 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.232 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 356/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 4613/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 993/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function cou